# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Blissful Abodes - AWS Configuration Template
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this section into your .env file and fill in the values

# === AWS CORE CREDENTIALS ===
# Generate from: https://console.aws.amazon.com/iam/home#/users
# Create an IAM user with S3, DynamoDB, EC2, IAM, and SNS permissions
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY
AWS_REGION=ap-south-1

# === AWS S3 CONFIGURATION ===
# Create bucket: aws s3 mb s3://blissful-abodes-media --region ap-south-1
S3_BUCKET=blissful-abodes-media
# Bucket will store:
# - images/                → Room photos
# - invoices/              → PDF invoices
# - qrcodes/               → Booking QR codes

# === AWS DynamoDB CONFIGURATION ===
# Create tables: See AWS_SERVICE_INTEGRATION.md
DYNAMODB_SESSIONS_TABLE=blissful-sessions
DYNAMODB_CHATBOT_TABLE=blissful-chatbot-history
DYNAMODB_AUDIT_TABLE=blissful-audit-logs
# Tables store:
# - Sessions: Flask session data (24h TTL)
# - Chatbot: Chat history (30-day TTL)
# - Audit: Compliance logs (permanent)

# === AWS EC2 CONFIGURATION ===
# Find these values from your EC2 instance:
# - Instance ID: AWS Console → EC2 → Instances
# - Instance Type: Usually t2.micro, t2.small, etc.
# - Public IP: Shown in instance details
EC2_INSTANCE_ID=i-0abc1234def56789
EC2_INSTANCE_TYPE=t2.micro
EC2_PUBLIC_IP=44.208.253.176

# === AWS IAM CONFIGURATION ===
# Create role: See AWS_SERVICE_INTEGRATION.md Step 4
IAM_INSTANCE_ROLE=blissful-abodes-ec2-role

# === AWS SNS CONFIGURATION ===
# Create topics: See AWS_SERVICE_INTEGRATION.md Step 5
# Get ARNs: aws sns list-topics --region ap-south-1
SNS_ADMIN_TOPIC_ARN=arn:aws:sns:ap-south-1:123456789012:blissful-admin-alerts
SNS_GUEST_TOPIC_ARN=arn:aws:sns:ap-south-1:123456789012:blissful-guest-notifications
# Topics send:
# - Admin: Fraud alerts, high-risk bookings, system alerts
# - Guest: Booking confirmations, reminders, check-in instructions

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP CHECKLIST
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

SETUP_CHECKLIST = """

✅ AWS SERVICES SETUP CHECKLIST
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Step 1: Create AWS Account & IAM User
□ Create AWS account (https://aws.amazon.com)
□ Create IAM user: blissful-abodes-app
□ Generate access key & secret access key
□ Save credentials securely

Step 2: Configure S3 (File Storage)
□ Create bucket: blissful-abodes-media
□ Enable public read for images
□ Configure CORS
□ Get bucket name for .env

Step 3: Configure DynamoDB (NoSQL Database)
□ Create table: blissful-sessions
  - PK: session_id (String)
  - TTL: 86400 (24 hours)
□ Create table: blissful-chatbot-history
  - PK: user_id (String), SK: timestamp (String)
  - TTL: 2592000 (30 days)
□ Create table: blissful-audit-logs
  - PK: user_id (String), SK: timestamp (String)
  - TTL: Disabled (permanent)

Step 4: Configure EC2 (Instance Monitoring)
□ Launch EC2 instance (AP South - Mumbai)
□ Attach IAM role: blissful-abodes-ec2-role
□ Get instance ID, type, and public IP
□ Save to .env

Step 5: Configure IAM (Identity Management)
□ Create role: blissful-abodes-ec2-role
□ Attach policy with S3, DynamoDB, EC2, SNS permissions
□ Create instance profile
□ Get role ARN for .env

Step 6: Configure SNS (Notifications)
□ Create SNS topic: blissful-admin-alerts
□ Create SNS topic: blissful-guest-notifications
□ Subscribe admin@blissfulabodes.com to admin topic
□ Confirm subscription (check email)
□ Get topic ARNs for .env

Step 7: Update .env File
□ Copy AWS_CONFIGURATION_TEMPLATE.env content
□ Fill in all AWS credentials
□ Fill in all service identifiers
□ Save as .env

Step 8: Test Integration
□ Run: python test_aws_services.py
□ Verify all services show ✅

Step 9: Deploy to EC2
□ SSH into EC2 instance
□ Clone repository
□ Install dependencies
□ Set .env variables
□ Run Flask app: python app.py

Step 10: Monitor & Optimize
□ Check CloudWatch metrics
□ Monitor DynamoDB usage
□ Check S3 bucket size
□ Optimize costs

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ESTIMATED COSTS (Monthly - Low Traffic)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Service             | Cost Estimate  | Notes
────────────────────┼────────────────┼──────────────────────────────
S3                  | $1-5           | Storage + data transfer
DynamoDB            | $2-10          | On-demand billing (pay per request)
EC2                 | $10-15         | t2.micro eligible for free tier
SNS                 | $1-2           | 1M notification estimate
IAM                 | FREE           | Always free
────────────────────┼────────────────┼──────────────────────────────
TOTAL               | $15-30         | Varies with traffic
────────────────────┼────────────────┼──────────────────────────────

